This product includes software developed by Subhash Rai for OnlineJourno
(https://onlinejourno.com).

Editorial frameworks referenced in this product:
- Project for Excellence in Journalism, "Framing the News" (1999)
- Deuze, M., "Online journalism: Modelling the first generation of news
  media on the World Wide Web", First Monday 6(10), 2001
- Reuters Institute, Digital News Report (annual)
- IPTC Media Topic codes (https://iptc.org/standards/media-topics/)

These frameworks are public methodologies; their use in this product is
non-exclusive and citation-only. No endorsement by the original authors
or institutions is implied or claimed.

OnlineJourno Xtnd capability tier (planned Y2+ release) extends the
above with additional editorial reference points:

- Reuters Institute, Digital News Report (annual) — distribution-surface
  baselines.
- News Product Alliance — converged-newsroom workflow patterns.
- Membership Puzzle Project — reader-engagement framing for
  subscription-fit modelling.
- Google News Initiative — Discover-readiness rubric (image aspect,
  structured data, freshness).

OnlineJourno Xtnd was briefly maintained as a separate repository
from 2026-06-03 through 2026-06-05;
content was merged into onlinejourno/newsroom on 2026-06-05 per
ADR 0030. The xtnd repository is archived with this history preserved.
